commit.message: Update for 0.5.47

request: limit probing after missing protocol

And do not consider HTTP/0.9 if there is too much junk afterward.

Avoids quadratic complexity with probing many whitespaces lines.

Ticket: 6757

Fixes: bf618ec7f243 ("http0.9: process headers if there are non-space characters")
Update for 0.5.46

tx: configurable number of maximum transactions

Ticket: #5921

htp: offers possibility to remove transactions

instead of keeping a null pointer

headers: limit the size of folded headers

Ticket: #6444

So as to limit the quadratic complexity of always reallocating
to push more bytes in header value

request: be more liberal about transfer-encoding value

For instance, the following header may be considered as valid:
Transfer-Encoding: chunked, chunked

Introduces a new helper function to recognize header value tokens

Ticket: #6415

request: continue processing even with invalid headers

So that following headers and response still get processed

Ticket: #6415

http0.9: process headers if there are non-space characters

Previously, we fell back on HTTP/0.9 if there was a missing protocol
except if the following line cintained a colon.

This makes libhtp stricter to consider a transaction as 0.9
by only accepting if we have spaces after the request line

as done in libhtp-rs

Ticket: 6643
htp_util: fix spelling issue
src: fix -Wshorten-64-to-32 warnings

uri: normalization removes trailing spaces

Ticket: #2881
Update for 0.5.45

log: resist allocation failure

If we cannot store the log message, simply return
support HTTP Bearer authentication
Update for 0.5.44

response: only trim spaces at headers names end

as is done for requests

response: skips lines before response line

Improve the logic for junk lines before response line, instead of
treating them as body, try to peek if the next line begins with
an H and may actually be the response line we were waiting for

If we do not see an H coming, we treat as if it were a HTTP/0.9
response to a HTTP1 request, that is a response without line and
headers but just directly body.
headers: log a warning for chunks extension
Update for 0.5.43

htp: do not log content-encoding: none

Ticket: #5757

htp: do not error on multiple 100 Continue

Ticket: #5917

readme: remove note on libhtp not being stable

It was noted in Suricata forum that it was still mentioned that libhtp
wasn't stable. It is considered stable, at this point.
